<li id="cite_note-18"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-18">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">"The very first question a biographer has to ask, namely when the person was born, cannot be answered precisely for Muhammad. [...] Muhammad's biographers usually make him 40 or sometimes 43 years old at the time of his call to be a prophet, which [...] would put the year of his birth at about 570 A.D." F.&#160;Buhl &amp; A.T.&#160;Welch, <i>Encyclopaedia of Islam 2nd ed.</i>, "Muhammad", vol.&#160;7, p.&#160;361.</span>
