<ul><li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://repository.library.georgetown.edu/handle/10822/552601">Islam and Politics</a> from the <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://repository.library.georgetown.edu/handle/10822/552494">Dean Peter Krogh Foreign Affairs Digital Archives</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://ssrn.com/abstract=1475928">Liberal Democracy and Political Islam: The Search for Common Ground</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20080216024026/http://www.salafimanhaj.com/pdf/SalafiManhaj_Terrorism_In_KSA.pdf">The Ideology of Terrorism and Violence in Saudi Arabia: Origins, Reasons and Solution</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.washington-report.org/backissues/0994/9409021.htm">Evaluating the Islamist movement</a> by Greg Noakes, an American Muslim who works at the <i>Washington Report</i>.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.washington-report.org/backissues/0695/9506017.htm">Muslim scholars face down fanaticism</a> by <a href="/wiki/Aicha_Lemsine" class="mw-redirect" title="Aicha Lemsine">Aicha Lemsine</a>, an Algerian journalist and author.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://cdm164001.cdmhost.com/krogh/item_viewer.php?CISOROOT=/p164001coll21&amp;CISOPTR=195&amp;CISOBOX=1&amp;REC=2">Peter Krogh discuses Islam and politics with John L. Esposito and Mary Jane Deeb</a> on <i>Great Decisions</i> (1994).</li></ul>
